fields.inlineHelpText: Indicates the type of Plan Requirement, for example, optional or required.
fields.label: Category
fields.name: hed__Category__c

fields.inlineHelpText: The Course associated with this Plan Requirement. Leave blank for a parent Plan Requirement with nested Plan Requirements.
fields.label: Course
fields.name: hed__Course__c

fields.inlineHelpText: The number of credits a student receives for satisfying this requirement.
fields.label: Credits
fields.name: hed__Credits__c

fields.inlineHelpText: If the Plan Requirement is one of multiple requirements or multiple levels of requirements, specifies the parent Plan Requirement. Use this field to group a list of optional Courses that satisfy a generic requirement.
fields.label: Parent Plan Requirement
fields.name: hed__Plan_Requirement__c

fields.inlineHelpText: The Program Plan this requirement is for. If you're grouping Plan Requirements together under a Parent Plan Requirement, best practice is to link only the top-level Plan Requirement to a Program Plan.
fields.label: Program Plan
fields.name: hed__Program_Plan__c

fields.inlineHelpText: This requirement's place in the Program Plan, for example, "1" indicates the first semester. Use this field to indicate the overall progression for the entire Program Plan, or to sort the order of sub-requirements within a single parent Plan Requirement.
fields.label: Sequence
fields.name: hed__Sequence__c
